famous.name: Vintage '65 Fender Super Reverb 45-Watt 4x10" Guitar Combo Amp
famous.description: Selling a vintage '65 Fender Super Reverb 2 Channel 40-Watt 4x10 Guitar Combo Amp.This is an incredibly clean example of this amp.The amp is in fantastic working condition and has that classic warm super reverb tone that you can only really get with an all original vintage amp like this.Was recently went through by an amp tech and has a clean bill of health with a 3 prong power cord also installed!Built in July of 1965 in Fullerton, California.Comes loaded with 4 - '65/'66 Jensen C10Q speakersLoaded with NOS Vintage GE 6L6 power tubes, Rectifier tube, and reissue mix of Groove and EHX preamp tubesOriginal Vinyl Cover and Footswitch included!Please, serious inquiries only!Will only respond to emails with a name and phone number!No Trades!Thanks!OverviewThe Fender Super Reverb 45-watt tube combo guitar amplifier was offered in a blackface finish between 1964 and 1967, although some early silverface finished units still had blackface circuitry. Well-known for its scooped mids, the Super Reverb features the same design as the Fender Super, but with the addition of built-in reverb and tremolo effects as well as four 10 speakers. Famous Super Reverb players include Johnny Marr, Stevie Ray Vaughan, Robben Ford, and Derek Trucks.
